entry.title: Felicia Schroeder (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that when Felicia Schroeder signed to play soccer for the University of South Carolina, the school did not have a sign-language interpreter available for her?

entry.title: a South Dakota TV station (Wikipedia — did you know?)

entry.title: Yusuf Meddah (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that a 14th-century work, originally attributed to another poet, was discovered in 2018 to be the creation of the Azerbaijani poet Yusuf Meddah?

entry.title: abortion in Taiwan (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that despite being legally available in most cases, abortion in Taiwan is still criminalized under the penal code?

entry.title: Jonathan Birch (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that a report by the philosopher Jonathan Birch and colleagues led to cephalopods and decapods being recognised as sentient under the UK's Animal Welfare (Sentience) Act?

entry.title: 2023 US FIBA Basketball World Cup team (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the 2023 US FIBA Basketball World Cup team is the first American national team of NBA players without an All-NBA player?

entry.title: Municipal Asphalt Plant (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the walls of the Municipal Asphalt Plant's mixing plant remained standing after three weeks of attempts to demolish it?
